[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Written evidence from Oil and Gas UK (HCS0007)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]1.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Oil &amp; Gas UK is the trade association that speaks for the whole sector and is the definitive source of information about the UK upstream. It serves as the 
[normal]gateway to industry networks and expertise.
[normal]1.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Offshore helicopter operations are routinely conducted in a hostile marine environment, hence the need to ensure that high levels of flight safety are pre-requisite.
[normal]1.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]No other country in which the oil and gas indu
[normal]stry operates puts more effort into improving its aviation safety performance through leadership, communication and co-operation.
[normal]1.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The UK industry recognises the importance of joined-up working and engages the workforce and trade unions in offshore helicopt
[normal]er safety awareness through offshore safety committees and onshore networks.
[normal]1.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Since 1992, six fatal accidents have claimed the lives of 47 offshore workers and flight crew and there have been 18 non-fatal accidents.
[normal]1.6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]However, to determine how safe offshore h
[normal]elicopter flights are requires an understanding of all facets of offshore helicopter flight operations and rotorcraft engineering.
[normal]1.7
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Comparisons between the safety performances of countries should be considered in relation to the measure of success in strivi
[normal]ng to meet the primary objective of ensuring that everything that can reasonably be done to minimise the risks is being done.
[normal]1.8
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Many safety initiatives have been funded and implemented by the oil and gas industry over the past 35 years.
[normal]1.9
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]This includes project
[normal]s jointly funded by oil and gas companies with the regulators (CAA and Health &amp; Safety Executive), helicopter operators and other involved organisations (e.g. National Air Traffic Service (NATS), aircraft and equipment manufacturers).
[normal]1.10
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Helicopter Task G
[normal]roup (HTG) and Helicopter Safety Steering Group (HSSG) are the other oil and gas industry groups dealing with helicopter operations but they serve different purposes. 
[normal]1.11
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Since the early days in the North Sea there has been almost constant regulatory evolutio
[normal]n. The current legislative basis for UK aviation flight operations and airworthiness are well established, of a high level, and kept under constant scrutiny by CAA.
[normal]1.12
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]As the regulatory spread of EASA continues to grow and increase its influence over UK 
[normal]aviation operations and airworthiness, etc. the UK Government should ensure that CAA resources and regulatory focus is properly maintained in order to reinforce CAA’s ability to continue applying high standards in UK aviation safety.
[normal]1.13
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]HSE regulate and has 
[normal]the oversight for helicopter activities on offshore installations. They do this in conjunction with CAA via a Memorandum of Understanding. HSE’s offshore inspectors effectively provide oversight of safety improvements to do with helideck operations
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Oil &amp; Gas UK is the leading representative body for the UK offshore oil and gas industry. It is a not-for-profit organisation, established in April 2007 but with a pedigree stretching back over 40 years.
[normal] 
[normal]Membership is open to all companies active
[normal] in the UK continental shelf
[normal] (UKCS)
[normal], from super majors to large contractor businesses and from independent oil companies to SMEs working in the supply chain.
[normal] Its predecessor was the UK Offshore Operators Association
[normal] (UKOOA)
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Our aim is to strengthen the l
[normal]ong-term health of the offshore oil and gas industry in the United Kingdom by working closely with companies across the sector, governments and all other stakeholders to address the issues that affect our business.
[normal]&#xa0;
